title: Moroccan-spiced Poussins With Saffron, Honey And Tomato Jam
summary: Moroccan-spiced Poussins With Saffron, Honey And Tomato Jam might be just the main course you are searching for. This gluten free, primal, and vegetarian recipe serves 4 and costs $3.49 per serving. One portion of this dish contains around 20g of protein, 38g of fat, and a total of 745 calories. 1 person has tried and liked this recipe. A mixture of saffron, blanched almonds, lemon juice, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so yummy. To use up the saffron you could follow this main course with the Creamy saffron yogurt as a dessert. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around 45 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 80%. This score is good. Try Moroccan-Spiced Cold Tomato Soup, Grilled Cod With Moroccan-spiced Tomato Relish, and Kefta Tajine (Moroccan Spiced Meatballs W/ Eggs in Tomato Sauce) for similar recipes.
